  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> of the lemongrass and set aside for later, then chop the <strong>softer inner core[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691060748092-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691060748092-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691060748092-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691060748092-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1691060748092-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and the <strong>outer lemongrass layers </strong>to a pot with a lid with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>and 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and discard the <strong>outer lemongrass layers </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691060750701-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691060750701-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691060750701-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691060750701-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1691060750701-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>inner lemongrass core</strong> and <strong>curry powder </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>,<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>marinated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1691060753252-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1691060753252-x400.jpg",
