          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1691060761992-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to a small bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>hot water</strong> and mix it all together until the sugar has dissolved</p><p>Add the<strong> remaining rice vinegar </strong>and<strong> tamarind paste</strong> to the bowl with the <strong>soy sauce</strong> and<strong> remaining chilli flakes</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chilli tamarind sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
